# TODO (Marky)

- [x] Value range semantics are undefined
  - The spec says matching is "under the class ordering" but the examples imply numeric semantics.
- [x] `<<sep>>` semantics are under-defined
  - `<<\n>>`, `<<>>`, `[**]<<>>[**]` don't follow a unified, coherent rule.
- [x] `[...]` is overloaded without disambiguation rules
  - Resolved: `{class}` prefix → value range, no prefix → literal, `:` → padding. Formalized in the Implicit Defaults table. Nested range slots fall out from root transparency — no behavioral consequence to disambiguate.
- [x] Does `<<sep>>` form a capture group?
  - Yes. Every `[...]` and `<<...>>` creates a capture group; this is now the core rule.
- [ ] Three-argument repetition range `2..n..5` is unexplained
- [ ] Alternation precedence is unspecified
  - `||` separates alternative patterns at any level" — but is `[a][b] || [c]` parsed as `([a][b]) || [c]` or `[a]([b] || [c])`?
- [x] Complement inside value ranges creates two exclusion syntaxes
  - Resolved: `{!...}` is character class complement (char-level); `,!value` / `,!min..max` inside `[...]` is value exclusion (string-level). Distinct purposes, no longer ambiguous.
- [ ] Formalize transformer chain nesting notation
- [ ] Define per-character exclusion syntax
  - `{a..z,!d..f}` appears in the spec as an example but the `,!char` mechanism inside `{...}` is never formally defined.
- [ ] Add second-layer shortcuts for common patterns
